Scope of the Reference Implementation

This release includes:

structural realization definitions
deterministic admissibility rules
structural carry-forward demonstrations
replay-safe realization outputs
reference traces and certificates

STRUPER defines a deterministic structural realization model where realization emerges from structure:

resolve(structure) ->

RESOLVED if structure is complete AND consistent
INCOMPLETE if structure is incomplete
CONFLICT if structure is inconsistent

What This Demonstrates

deterministic structural realization evolution
structural carry-forward
replay-safe realization continuity
realization evolution through structural extension
independence from procedural realization flow as correctness source
deterministic and reproducible realization states
identical structure produces identical realization and certificate
Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible if it preserves:

structure-based correctness
deterministic realization resolution
structural carry-forward
deterministic replay behavior
structure-driven realization visibility
reproducibility of realization and certificate under equivalent inputs
explicit handling of incomplete and conflicting structure

Conformance is judged solely by observable behavior — not by internal implementation.

S1 = S2 -> Realization1 = Realization2 -> Certificate1 = Certificate2

Conflict Handling

In this reference implementation:

CONFLICT is explicitly defined and demonstrated
INCOMPLETE corresponds to structurally insufficient realization declarations
inconsistent conditions do not produce visible realization

Conformance requires:

no forced realization under incomplete structure
no arbitrary realization under conflicting structure

Normalization Requirement

For deterministic certificate identity:

normalized_realization = normalize(Realization)

certificate = hash(normalized_realization)

Normalization ensures:

independence from procedural realization flow
independence from representation format
consistent certificate identity across runs and systems

In the reference implementation:

SHA-256 is used for demonstration.

Deterministic Replay Guarantee

Correctness remains invariant under replay:

same structure -> same realization -> same output certificate

This ensures:

replay != divergence

Realization depends only on structure — not procedural realization sequencing.

Structural Evolution Principle

STRUPER demonstrates:

small structural extension -> deterministic upgraded realization

without reconstructing mature realization structure.

This enables:

structural carry-forward
replay-safe structural evolution
deterministic realization continuity
reusable realization foundations

Relationship to Shunyaya Framework

STRUPER is part of the broader Shunyaya framework.

It builds on:

SLANG -> correctness without execution
ORL -> correctness without ordering
STIME -> correctness without synchronized time
STINT -> correctness without connectivity
STILE -> correctness without communication
SVARE -> correctness without computation
STOCRS -> correctness without sequence or synchronization
STOCRS-R -> realization-path independence
STRUMER -> structural media realization
STRUPER -> structural realization beyond procedural realization dependence

Each removes an assumed dependency for correctness.
Correctness remains preserved by structure.

