Closing Statement

STRUPER explores a simple but fundamental idea:

Bounded realization correctness may emerge deterministically from structure — without requiring procedural realization flow as the source of correctness.

Procedural systems may reveal realization.
Structure determines admissibility.

It is released to encourage:

independent validation
real-world testing
safe experimentation

STRUPER is offered as a minimal, verifiable reference implementation of that possibility.
